3.2. Working With LocalTime
The LocalTime represents time without a date.
Similar to LocalDate, we can create an instance of LocalTime from the system clock or by using parse
and of methods.
Finally, the max, min and noon time of a day can be obtained by constants in LocalTime class.
This is very useful when performing database queries to find records within a given span of time.
For example, the below code represents 23:59:59.99:
LocalTime maxTime = LocalTime.MAX